<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="479" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="3.[831,1436,1204,1292]" pageId="3" pageNumber="479">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[831,965,1205,1229]" pageId="3" pageNumber="479">Etymology:</emphasis>
The name is derived from the Latin 
<emphasis box="[831,951,1236,1260]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="479">oblungus-a</emphasis>
= very elongated, and refers to the shape of the valva in the male genitalia.
</paragraph>
